  "texts": [
    "Interplay of flavor, collider, and EW data: a motivated exampleTo illustrate the role of precision measurements in flavor physics in the near future, we focus on the rare decays B + → K + ν ν and K + → π + ν ν, exploring their interplay with related electroweak and collider observables.",
    "These rare processes hold particular interest for a series of reasons: i) they are theoretically clean, making it straightforward to interpret possible deviations from the SM; ii) the measurements of the corresponding decay rates are expected to improve significantly in the next 10-15 years; iii) they are sensitive to a limited number of effective operators, allowing for a simple EFT interpretation; iv) the present central values exceed the corresponding SM predictions (with different degrees of significance), allowing for speculation about possible beyond-the-SM contributions.Using the experimental inputs and SM predictions described in section 3.1, present experimental results, normalized to the corresponding SM predictions, are as follows:B(B + → K + ν ν) exp B(B + → K + ν ν) SM = 2.8 ± 0.8, B(K + → π + ν ν) exp B(K + → π + ν ν) SM = 1.23 ± 0.39.",
    "(5.1)In the U(2) 5 -symmetric SMEFT, flavor violation is limited to left-handed quarks.",
    "The low-energy effective Lagrangian describing b → sν ν and s → dν ν transitions at the partonic level can be conveniently normalized asL d i →d j ν ν = 4G F √ 2 α W 2π V * ts V tb C sbℓ L (s L γ µ b L) + V * td V ts C dsℓ L ( dL γ µ s L) × (ν ℓ L γ µ ν ℓ L),(5.2)where 4πα W = g 2 L. Given the absence of QCD and QED contributions to the anomalous dimensions of these effective operators, we can determine possible NP contributions via a simple tree-level matching to the SMEFT.",
    "Decomposing theC ijℓ L as C ijℓ L ≡ C ijℓ L,SM + ∆C ijℓ L, this leads to ∆C ijℓ L = πv 2 α W V * ti V tj [L V,LL νd] ℓℓij,(5.3)where[L V,LL νd] ℓℓij = [L † d] ip C (1)[ℓℓpr] ℓq -C (3)[ℓℓpr] ℓq + C (1)[pr] Hq + C (3)[pr] Hq [L d] rj."
